race.comment: Very tricky. FUTURE HISTORY (4) was much better last time in the G3 Coongy Cup at Cauflield when sticking on well for third as the winner had the perfect run. He sets up very nicely on speed from barrier two with Zahra sticking. Not sure what to do with MIDDLE EARTH (1). He'd been just slowly building and was fancied to win the G1 Caulfield Cup last week out to 2400m but was disappointing in 11th. Back in trip now on the quick turnaround and likely to concede a big start, but ability wise he is well placed. CASINO SEVENTEEN (3) bounced back to form in the Coongy, second at big odds there when beating home FUTURE HISTORY. Has to be respected now. NAVAL COLLEGE (6) improved nicely second up and drops 6kg off that. Can sneak into the finish. SIR KINGSFORD (8) can race on speed and give a sight.
